title: Iran's assistance to Russian war effort could make the country an enemy combatant, experts say
description: Iran has supplied Russia with drones and other military equipment for its war in Ukraine that could open the country up to being considered a combatant in the conflict.

title: In midterm elections, women's votes will decide our future
description: Women are the most powerful voting bloc in the nation, and we have the power and the determination to shape the future of this country on Election Day.

title: Biden’s history of berating, scolding and insulting reporters, from ‘stupid son of a b---h’ to ‘get educated’
description: President Biden scolded reporters who pressed him campaign trail appearances and abortion restrictions last week, continuing his tradition of barking at journalists.

title: Biden’s ‘official’ trips as president land him in places with tight campaign races too
description: President Biden’s official White House trips in recent weeks have been scheduled on the same days and in the same areas as political events, which helps defray costs incurred by Democratic political operations for campaign-related activity.

title: Kevin Spacey found not liable in Anthony Rapp sex abuse case: A look at the allegations against him
description: Although Kevin Spacey was found not liable in the sexual abuse case brought against him by Anthony Rapp, the "House of Cards" actor still faces another trial in the United Kingdom.

title: Australian men face charges after blinding e-scooter rider with projectile potato
description: Two men in Australia were arrested and charged after firing potatoes at people riding e-scooters. A young man was hit in the face and had to have surgery to remove one of his eyes.

title: Astros complete sweep of Yankees, will face Phillies in World Series
description: The Houston Astros are still the team to beat in the American League. They completed their sweep of the New York Yankees and will face the Phillies in the World Series.

title: On this day in history, Oct. 24, 1861, transcontinental telegraph completed, connecting coasts for first time
description: The transcontinental telegraph was completed on Oct. 24, 1861, making possible instant communication between the coasts possible for the first time. It rendered the Pony Express obsolete.

title: Dolphins earn win over Steelers in Tua Tagovailoa's return
description: The Miami Dolphins snapped a three-game losing streak on Sunday against the Pittsburgh Steelers with the return of quarterback Tua Tagovailoa, who previously suffered a concussion.

title: Ellison denies knowing anyone who supports defunding police despite own support for replacing police force
description: Minnesota Attorney General Keith Ellison claimed that he didn't know anyone who supports the "Defund the Police" movement despite previous support for replacing police.

title: Yankees' Nestor Cortes leaves do-or-die Game 4 with injury
description: With the Yankees on the verge of being swept in the American League Championship Series, Nestor Cortes left the game with an injury in the third inning.

title: 'Welcome to Plathville' star, Kim Plath, arrested for DUI in Florida: report
description: "Welcome to Plathville" matriarch Kim Plath turned herself in to the Wakulla County Sheriff's Office and was arrested for DUI stemming from a crash in June

title: Michigan family of four that mysteriously disappeared one week ago is located in Wisconsin
description: A Michigan family that disappeared on Oct. 16 after the father displayed "paranoia" during a 911 call was located in Wisconsin on Sunday, police announced.

title: Washington Senate: Murray calls for gun control after being accused of being soft on crime during debate
description: Sen. Patty Murray defended her record against Republican challenger Tiffany Smiley during Sunday's debate as she looks to hold on a seat she has held since 1993.

title: Gov. Bill Lee points to the open border as being one of the sources of crime plaguing the nation's streets
description: Tennessee Gov. Bill Lee, R, spoke about his efforts to combat crime and boost police in his state while appearing on “Sunday Night in America with Trey Gowdy.”

title: Michigan grandmother allegedly stabbed 2-year-old grandson in head, boy recovering in hospital
description: A Michigan grandmother is accused of stabbing her 2-year-old grandson in the head multiple times. The boy is in stable condition in a local hospital.

title: Virginia high school reports illness outbreak, 1,000 students call out sick
description: Around 1,000 students and a few staff members at a Virginia high school called out sick last week after experiencing flu-like symptoms and stomach pains.

title: 'America is being destroyed' by the Democratic Party: Mark Levin
description: Mark Levin says Democrats are destorying the country by challenging America's foundational values from within in his opening monologue on 'Life, Liberty & Levin.'

title: Philadelphia Phillies fans go crazy celebrating team going to World Series
description: The Philadelphia Phillies are headed to their first World Series since 2009 after missing the postseason for 11 years. Fans are making up for lost time.

title: Josh Jacobs' hat trick propels Raiders over Texans
description: Josh Jacobs ran for 143 yards and three touchdowns, all in the second half, as the Las Vegas Raiders took down the Houston Texans on Sunday.

title: Seahawks rookie running back shines in blowout win over Chargers
description: The Seattle Seahawks offense continued to dominate, this time in Los Angeles, as they defeated the Chargers thanks to a huge day from Kenneth Walker.

title: Jets win fourth in a row, but at an immense cost, as Broncos falter again
description: The New York Jets won their fourth game in a row, adding to the Denver Broncos' misery, but it come at the cost of likely losing Breece Hall for the year.

title: US, Russian defense secretaries speak for second time in three days amid 'dirty bomb' claims
description: Lloyd Austin, the U.S. Secretary of Defense, spoke with his Russian counterpart for the second time in three days on Sunday, according to the Pentagon.

title: Patrick Mahomes' big day spoils Christian McCaffrey's 49ers debut
description: The San Francisco 49ers got a huge jolt when they acquired Christian McCaffrey, but the Kansas City Chiefs were just too much for them to handle.

title: 'Face the Nation' focus groups of GOP, Democrat parents sound off on 'woke culture' overtaking US education
description: A CBS focus group of parents agreed that 'woke' school curriculums have become a main concern for them and will be a voting priority in the upcoming midterms.
